@Node "> History" "ProNET.guide/> History"
@Toc "Main"

History
=======

   This section only lists the most important changes.  A more profound
text can be found in the @{b}ChangeLog@{ub} file.

Version 3.4
-----------

   released on 29-May-1999. No actual code changes, but removed the
Shareware requesters and added the complete source code to the
distribution.

Version 3.3
-----------

   released on 17-May-98. No actual code changes, only the documentation
has been fixed in some places (addresses).

Version 3.2
-----------

   released on 27-Jan-97 including pronet.device @{i}38.0@{ui}, pronet-handler
@{i}38.0@{ui}, pronet-server @{i}38.0@{ui}, pronet-start @{i}37.0@{ui}, pronet-stop @{i}38.0@{ui},
pronet-flush @{i}36.0@{ui}, pronet-talk @{i}37.1@{ui}, pronet-run @{i}37.0@{ui}, pronet-page @{i}37.0@{ui},
internal-parallel @{i}37.0@{ui}, mfc-parallel @{i}37.0@{ui}, serial @{i}37.0@{ui}.

   @{b}*@{ub} pronet-stop removes the device node completely now; a restart with
     the same name is possible!

   @{b}*@{ub} Icons appear earlier on the Workbench than in previous versions.

   @{b}*@{ub} pronet-stop UNIT keyword (dismount all devices on that Unit)

   @{b}*@{ub} Small bug fixes.

Version 3.1
-----------

   released on 30-Nov-96 including pronet.device @{i}37.2@{ui}, pronet-handler
@{i}37.1@{ui}, pronet-server @{i}37.0@{ui}, pronet-start @{i}37.0@{ui}, pronet-stop @{i}36.1@{ui},
pronet-flush @{i}36.0@{ui}, pronet-talk @{i}37.1@{ui}, pronet-run @{i}37.0@{ui}, pronet-page @{i}37.0@{ui},
internal-parallel @{i}37.0@{ui}, mfc-parallel @{i}37.0@{ui}, serial @{i}37.0@{ui}.

   @{b}*@{ub} Major Bugfix: Crash when starting ProNET.

   @{b}*@{ub} Major Bugfix: Disksalv and Workbench/NewDrawer now work correctly.

   @{b}*@{ub} Server reboot partly implemented, but it's still being developed.
     Consider this kind of beta.

   @{b}*@{ub} Changed transfer protocols and device API -> incompatible to
     ProNET V3!

   @{b}*@{ub} ...and some other goodies.

Version 3
---------

   released on 23-Aug-96 including pronet.device @{i}36.6@{ui}, pronet-handler
@{i}36.4@{ui}, pronet-server @{i}36.4@{ui}, pronet-start @{i}36.3@{ui}, pronet-stop @{i}36.1@{ui},
pronet-flush @{i}36.0@{ui}, pronet-talk @{i}36.0@{ui}, pronet-run @{i}36.1@{ui}, pronet-page @{i}36.0@{ui},
internal-parallel @{i}36.1@{ui}, mfc-parallel @{i}36.0@{ui}, serial @{i}36.2@{ui}.

   @{b}*@{ub} No more MountList and ProNET.config fiddling, @{b}pronet-start@{ub} does
     everything now! Thus, @{b}pronet-handler@{ub} had to be changed, too.

   @{b}*@{ub} Wrote a MultiFaceCard3 driver.

   @{b}*@{ub} Debugged the serial driver.

   @{b}*@{ub} Network can be shut down without having to reset.

   @{b}*@{ub} Completely new documentation.

   @{b}*@{ub} The @{b}serial@{ub} driver can be advised to use 3-wire cables now.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added commandline checkings to @{b}pronet-page@{ub} and @{b}pronet-run@{ub}.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}pronet-talk@{ub} uses fixed port 1994.

   @{b}*@{ub} New @{b}pronet.device@{ub} error code @{b}PNDERR_UNIT_NOT_DEFINED@{ub}, fixed unit
     open failure handling.

Version 2.1
-----------

   (bugfix) released on 08-Jul-95 including pronet-talk @{i}34.2@{ui},
pronet-server @{i}35.0@{ui}.

   @{b}*@{ub} pronet-talk AND pronet-server didn't accept the UNIT argument...

Version 2
---------

   released on 24-Jun-95 including pronet.device @{i}35.4@{ui}, pronet-handler
@{i}34.2@{ui}, pronet-server @{i}34.9@{ui}, pronet-talk @{i}34.1@{ui}, pronet-run @{i}34.1@{ui},
pronet-page @{i}34.0@{ui}.

   @{b}*@{ub} If the main machine resets, there is no need to reset the server
     any more.

   @{b}*@{ub} The device doesn't freeze the machine.

   @{b}*@{ub} Priority of transfer process can be set now

   @{b}*@{ub} Disk change recognition improved again

   @{b}*@{ub} Completely new documentation

   @{b}*@{ub} READ-actions are now transferred splitted, and don't require as
     much RAM on the server as in V1.

   @{b}*@{ub} EXAMINE-Packets could cause memory loss on the server

   @{b}*@{ub} Completely new pronet.device, with modular driver concept

   @{b}*@{ub} "+"-Expansion >> Unitnumber

   @{b}*@{ub} C include file

   @{b}*@{ub} everything I forgot to write here

   @{b}*@{ub} Lots of bug fixes, thus a lot more stable

Version 1
---------

   released on 01-Nov-94 (initial release) including pronet.device
@{i}33.9@{ui}, pronet-handler @{i}33.5@{ui}, pronet-server @{i}33.5@{ui}, pronet-talk
@{i}33.0@{ui}, pronet-run @{i}33.0@{ui}, pronet-page @{i}33.0@{ui}.

Version 0
---------

   I got the idea for `ProNET' in December 1993 after being
disappointed by ParNet and started programming the device in April 1994.


@EndNode

@Node "FAQ" "ProNET.guide/FAQ"
@Toc "Main"

FAQ - Frequently Asked Questions
********************************

   @{b}*@{ub} Is it possible to stop the network in order to do some printing
     and then reconnect both Amigas via a parallel port switch?

     No, this is not possible, and it will not be in future, because the
     network relies on the parallel port registers not to be changed by
     the Operating System.

   @{b}*@{ub} Is there a possibility to start a program on the remote machine and
     see its output in a CON:-Window on the main machine?

     No, this is not possible as yet, but will perhaps be implemented in
     the future.

   @{b}*@{ub} Is it possible to use the serial port of the remote machine to e.g.
     connect a second modem or using a MIDI interface and a modem at the
     same time?

     This is a thing which is on my to-do list.  Thanks to Giovanni
     Gigante for the nice idea!

   @{b}*@{ub} Will the `pronet-handler' ever run on Kickstarts earlier than 2.0?

     No.

   @{b}*@{ub} Would a special 020/030/040/060 version of the device or the
     drivers improve `ProNET''s speed?

     No.

   @{b}*@{ub} I've discovered a bug: When I reset the main computer and mount all
     network devices again, I can continue working without problems.
     However, when I reset the machine on which pronet-server is running
     and start pronet-server again, the network is dead.

     This is no bug, because the pronet-server creates some structures
     for the main machine which are cleared if you reset the server
     machine! A conclusion from that is, that `crossed-over' networks,
     where both machines are server and client, are not allowed to do a
     reset at all!  This is an essential difference between `ProNET'
     and professional network packages.

   @{b}*@{ub} Can pronet.device used as an interface driver for SANA-II compliant
     network software?

     No, this is not possible, since my device is not SANA-II compliant
     :) However, I intend to code a device stub so you could use all
     ProNET drivers with e.g. Envoy or AmiTCP.

   @{b}*@{ub} Why didn't I program my device SANA-II compliant??

     This is because when I started programming `ProNET', I didn't know
     that this standard existed.

   @{b}*@{ub} Do I have to call @{b}pronet-start@{ub} for every drive or can I somehow
     combine calls for more than one device?

     No. Create a shell script if you are too lazy ;-)

   @{b}*@{ub} I use a CDTV / A500+A570 as a server. The CD-ROM drive seems not
     to recognize disk changes. Is it a bug in `ProNET'?

     No, it's a bug in the CDTV file system. Simply issue a @{b}diskchange
     cd0:@{ub} command on the client or server machine.

   @{b}*@{ub} I use the Workbench to copy large files to the server. Sometimes
     the computer says 'not enough memory'.

     Try to use the Shell copy command or a DOpus like tool instead.
     Explanation for programmers:  Large ACTION_WRITEs lead to
     problems, since a corresponding amount of memory needs to be
     allocated on the server machine.  Writing step-by-step is too
     dangerous in disk-nearly-full situations.

   Hmm...  sorry that there were not too much questions I could answer
with a simple `Yes' :) ohh well but let me think about that again...
ahhh here it is:

   @{b}*@{ub} Is `ProNET' better than ParNet?

     <Guess> :-)


@EndNode

